### AgentLens API examples
### Run the backend with:
###   SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=local ./mvnw spring-boot:run
### The local profile enables demo traffic plus the API keys below.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@json = application/json
@ingestKey = ingest-local-key
@operatorKey = operator-local-key

### 0) Public landing endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: application/json

### 1) Public health endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/health
Accept: application/json

### 2) Create an operator-managed agent
### Copy the returned `id` into `@agentId` below.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/agents
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "name": "approval-demo-agent",
  "description": "Exercises approval and policy flows",
  "owner": "ops@agentlens.dev"
}

@agentId = REPLACE_WITH_AGENT_ID

### 3) Start a trace
### Copy the returned `id` into `@traceId`.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/traces
X-API-Key: {{ingestKey}}
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "agentId": "{{agentId}}",
  "model": "gpt-4o",
  "promptText": "Review the deployment plan and decide whether to execute the shell command.",
  "tenantId": "tenant-acme",
  "sessionId": "session-approval"
}

@traceId = REPLACE_WITH_TRACE_ID

### 4) Add a risky tool event
### This should match the seeded shell approval policy and move the trace into PENDING_APPROVAL.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/traces/{{traceId}}/events
X-API-Key: {{ingestKey}}
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "eventType": "TOOL_CALL",
  "eventName": "execShell",
  "inputData": {
    "command": "kubectl rollout restart deployment/payments"
  },
  "outputData": {
    "status": "queued"
  },
  "status": "SUCCESS",
  "durationMs": 82
}

### 5) List pending approvals
### Copy the relevant violation `id` into `@violationId`.
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/violations?actionTaken=PENDING_APPROVAL&page=0&size=20
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Accept: application/json

@violationId = REPLACE_WITH_VIOLATION_ID

### 6a) Approve the violation and let the trace continue
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/violations/{{violationId}}/approve
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "resolvedBy": "admin@agentlens.dev"
}

### 6b) Reject the violation instead
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/violations/{{violationId}}/reject
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "resolvedBy": "admin@agentlens.dev",
  "reason": "Rejected because shell access was not justified"
}

### 7) Complete the trace after approval
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/traces/{{traceId}}/complete
X-API-Key: {{ingestKey}}
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "responseText": "The deployment step was approved and completed successfully.",
  "inputTokens": 1800,
  "outputTokens": 420,
  "groundingScore": 0.88,
  "ttftMs": 140
}

### 8) Fetch the trace detail
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/traces/{{traceId}}
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Accept: application/json

### 9) Fetch the trace timeline
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/traces/{{traceId}}/timeline
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Accept: application/json

### 10) List policies
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/policies?page=0&size=50
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Accept: application/json

### 11) Create a custom approval policy
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/policies
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "name": "Shell Approval Gate",
  "description": "Pause traces before shell tools execute",
  "policyType": "REQUIRE_APPROVAL",
  "config": {
    "for_tools": ["execShell"],
    "approvers": ["admin@agentlens.dev"]
  },
  "scope": "GLOBAL",
  "severity": "BLOCK"
}

### 12) Dry-run policy evaluation without starting a real trace
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/policies/evaluate
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "agentId": "{{agentId}}",
  "model": "gpt-4o",
  "promptText": "Run a shell command to restart production.",
  "events": [
    {
      "eventType": "TOOL_CALL",
      "eventName": "execShell",
      "inputData": {
        "command": "deploy.sh"
      },
      "outputData": {
        "status": "pending"
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 13) Analytics summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/summary
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Accept: application/json

### 14) Analytics cost by model
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/cost?groupBy=model
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Accept: application/json

### 15) Analytics latency
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/latency
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Accept: application/json

### 16) Analytics violations
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/violations
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Accept: application/json

### 17) Audit log
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/audit?page=0&size=20
X-API-Key: {{operatorKey}}
Accept: application/json
